if you only look for 1 review site, yes....but like i told..google is your friend:




 
ofc, each reviewer have their own parameters. almost all reviews on battery drain go mostly for video because it's faster to drain battery that way. in video htc u11 is pretty bad because of 1440p screen, but it is very efficient browsing web or listening to music (which is 90% of the time i pass with the phone). all people i know that had or have both phones (s8 and htc u11) said htc u11 battery last longer than samsung s8, so i guess i prefer a real life review than a synthetic benchmark. if you only watch videos on the smartphone, probably htc u11 is not your best friend. in my case, the htc u11 is way better than my previews htc 10. with the things i do i can have more half a day easily. i never worried about battery in this phone and never let me down. 
 
note: there are lots of things you can disable in your smartphone to improve the smartphone standby time. usually that's the first thing i do when i've a new smartphone. don't know how fair are these comparisons because i don't know on them what is ON or OFF.  what i know is that i can have 2 day battery life easy on my htc u11. usually i end up with more than 50% battery at the end of the day. i'm not a smartphone gamer, but i use it a lot to manage 2 email accounts, web browsing and testing apps (i'm a app developer).
